♪ For the Lord God
Omnipotent reigneth

26
00:05:57,200 --> 00:06:00,870
♪ Hallelujah

27
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:03,520
♪ And he shall reign for ever and ever

28
00:06:03,820 --> 00:06:05,520
I never really enjoyed The Messiah.

29
00:06:05,620 --> 00:06:08,370
In fact, I think it's fucking boring.

30
00:06:08,540 --> 00:06:13,800
But your voice makes even a hack
like Handel seem like a genius.

31
00:06:14,970 --> 00:06:18,640
♪ Hallelujah, hallelujah

32
00:06:18,770 --> 00:06:20,890
♪ Hallelujah, hallelujah

33
00:06:20,980 --> 00:06:23,190
♪ Hallelujah

34
00:06:23,350 --> 00:06:25,520
♪ Hallelujah, hallelujah

35
00:06:25,650 --> 00:06:32,950
♪ Hallelujah

36
00:06:33,780 --> 00:06:36,120
Victor... When we...
When we put this thing to bed,

37
00:06:36,280 --> 00:06:38,620
you can brand the
Fourth Amendment on my butt.

38
00:06:38,790 --> 00:06:42,290
- Thank you.
- Sir, excuse me. Your wife is on line one.

39
00:06:42,460 --> 00:06:46,130
Sean! A jet was just chartered.
Anderson Airfield.

40
00:06:46,250 --> 00:06:48,840
Guess who paid the bill in cash?
Pollux Troy.

41
00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,800
- Put one of our people on that plane.
- Wait! We still got no sign of Castor!

42
00:06:51,970 --> 00:06:54,830
Pollux doesn't fly without
Big Brother. Now come on!

43
00:07:36,140 --> 00:07:40,510
You're 26 minutes late.
The casing didn't fit, right?

44
00:07:40,680 --> 00:07:43,520
Yeah, I told you goddam Dietrich
would try to pawn off some...

45
00:07:43,680 --> 00:07:45,730
cheap-shit North Korean plastic.

46
00:07:45,900 --> 00:07:48,900
Casing fit like a condom.

47
00:07:49,060 --> 00:07:52,400
You didn't deviate
from the plan, did you, Pollux?

48
00:07:52,570 --> 00:07:55,240
Well, how long did you want me
to sit here twiddling my thumbs?

49
00:07:55,360 --> 00:07:59,070
I paid for the jet.
Save us some time.

50
00:07:59,240 --> 00:08:03,660
That's what the boys are for,
to hide our famous faces.

51
00:08:13,010 --> 00:08:15,670
If I didn't love you so damn
much, I'd have to kill you, bro.

52
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:18,470
I hate it when you call me bro.

53
00:08:27,480 --> 00:08:29,520
You guys are paid
to protect him from everybody,

54
00:08:29,650 --> 00:08:31,900
including himself.

55
00:08:32,070 --> 00:08:36,610
And stay away from downtown on the 18th.
It's gonna be a little, um, smoggy.

56
00:08:40,030 --> 00:08:41,870
Okay, my passengers are here.
I gotta go.

57
00:08:47,250 --> 00:08:49,960
Let's go. Let's go.
I'm bored. Let's go.

58
00:08:50,130 --> 00:08:52,800
- Here you go.
- Bravo.

59
00:08:52,920 --> 00:08:55,710
Would you like anything else
once we're airborne?

60
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:57,930
Oh, a peach.

61
00:08:59,890 --> 00:09:02,810
Sit. Come here.

62
00:09:07,270 --> 00:09:10,900
You know, I can, uh,
eat a peach for hours.

63
00:09:13,770 --> 00:09:16,240
Um, come here.

64
00:09:16,400 --> 00:09:20,910
If I were to send you flowers,
where would I, uh...

65
00:09:21,120 --> 00:09:23,580
No, wait. Let me rephrase.

66
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:28,040
If I were to let you
suck my tongue,

67
00:09:29,330 --> 00:09:32,210
would you be grateful?

68
00:09:53,730 --> 00:09:55,900
There's someone on the runway.

69
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:02,070
Get off of me!

70
00:10:15,500 --> 00:10:18,460
- Archer.
- FBI!

71
00:10:24,760 --> 00:10:28,180
This is a very big gun.
Fly the fuckin' plane!

72
00:10:32,310 --> 00:10:34,520
Come on. That's it.

73
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:42,110
- Come on. Let's go!
- Goddam it. Don't play chicken with a goddam jet!

74
00:10:46,120 --> 00:10:48,120
Come on.

75
00:10:54,170 --> 00:10:58,130
- He's got Winters! Goddam it!
- Damn it, Sean!

76
00:11:08,600 --> 00:11:11,270
All units, pin 'em in!

77
00:11:13,020 --> 00:11:15,310
Close in on 'em!

78
00:11:21,570 --> 00:11:24,030
One of yours, Sean?

79
00:11:26,070 --> 00:11:27,830
Shit!

80
00:11:41,590 --> 00:11:44,680
Out. Come on. Go, go!

81
00:11:47,010 --> 00:11:48,930
Goddam it, Sean!

82
00:12:01,070 --> 00:12:03,940
Take off now.

83
00:12:09,160 --> 00:12:12,080
- Fly!
- I can't!

84
00:12:12,290 --> 00:12:14,750
Fly, bitch!

85
00:12:26,880 --> 00:12:29,720
All units, locked and ready.
Follow Archer's lead.

86
00:12:39,690 --> 00:12:41,650
What the fuck are you doing?

87
00:12:41,770 --> 00:12:44,940
There's an engine out.
We gotta stop.

88
00:13:31,410 --> 00:13:33,410
- Move, move, move!
- Get back! Back up!

89
00:14:05,860 --> 00:14:08,320
Pollux!

90
00:14:11,700 --> 00:14:13,620
- Cas!
- Get over here.

91
00:14:15,530 --> 00:14:17,500
Back him to me.
Back him to me. He's mine!

92
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:31,970
Cas.

93
00:14:35,930 --> 00:14:37,810
Secure the hangar.

94
00:15:03,830 --> 00:15:05,960
Berkley, down!

95
00:15:20,140 --> 00:15:22,850
Down!

96
00:16:06,600 --> 00:16:08,940
Give up, Castor. Your time's up.

97
00:16:11,280 --> 00:16:14,570
Well, you better hit me, Sean,
'cause you only got one bullet left.

98
00:16:14,740 --> 00:16:17,410
So do you.

99
00:16:17,530 --> 00:16:22,200
Wow. We've got
something in common.

100
00:16:22,330 --> 00:16:24,620
We both know our guns.

101
00:16:24,790 --> 00:16:29,540
What we don't have in common is that
I don't care if I live, and you do.

102
00:16:29,670 --> 00:16:33,550
Sean, that hurts.

103
00:16:33,670 --> 00:16:36,220
You're not having
any fun, are you, Sean?

104
00:16:36,340 --> 00:16:39,050
Why don't you come with us?
Try terrorism for hire?

105
00:16:39,180 --> 00:16:41,720
- We'll blow some shit up. It's more fun.
- Shut the fuck up.

106
00:16:41,850 --> 00:16:44,430
You watch your fuckin' mouth!

107
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:48,770
I'm about to unleash
the biblical plague "Hell-A" deserves,

108
00:16:48,940 --> 00:16:51,480
but I'll give this shithole
a break if my brother and I walk.

109
00:16:51,650 --> 00:16:55,860
- Bullshit.
- Oh-Oh no, I-I see, I see. Y-You think I'm bluffing.

110
00:16:55,990 --> 00:16:59,410
Maybe I am.
But, then, maybe I'm not.

111
00:16:59,570 --> 00:17:01,830
More importantly, what would
you do with me locked up?

112
00:17:01,990 --> 00:17:04,200
You'd drive your wife
and kid crazy.

113
00:17:04,330 --> 00:17:06,410
Say, how is your daughter,
anyway? Is she ripening by now?

114
00:17:06,580 --> 00:17:09,080
Your... Your darling Janie,
your little peach?

115
00:17:09,250 --> 00:17:11,920
Is she ripe?

116
00:17:14,670 --> 00:17:16,510
Okay.

117
00:17:16,670 --> 00:17:18,930
O-Okay.

118
00:17:19,090 --> 00:17:21,260
Policeman, don't shoot me.

119
00:17:23,430 --> 00:17:26,180
I'm scared, Seanie!

120
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:31,360
Well, I think you better pull
the trigger,

121
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:33,360
because I don't give a fuck!

122
00:17:33,520 --> 00:17:35,820
<i>♪ I'm ready ♪</i>

123
00:17:36,030 --> 00:17:39,740
<i>♪ Ready for the big ride, baby ♪</i>

124
00:18:08,180 --> 00:18:12,100
Well, Sean, looks like
Elvis done left the buildin'.

125
00:18:24,530 --> 00:18:28,500
It wasn't my fault.
Why won't you ever be on my side?

126
00:18:28,660 --> 00:18:31,870
I am always on your side,
but you have to give me a chance...

127
00:18:32,040 --> 00:18:34,290
Now what?

128
00:18:34,460 --> 00:18:37,420
She was suspended again. Some kid
made a crack about her clothes...

129
00:18:37,550 --> 00:18:40,550
- She started a fight.
- That's right, Dad. Don't even ask me what happened.

130
00:18:40,720 --> 00:18:43,390
Okay. What happened?

131
00:18:49,060 --> 00:18:53,270
- Ah, I see.
- Not like you would believe me anyway.

132
00:18:53,400 --> 00:18:55,980
Jamie, look,
it-it-it's not easy, okay?

133
00:18:56,110 --> 00:19:00,280
I mean, loo... You change the way
you look every week.

134
00:19:00,400 --> 00:19:04,910
And-And the way you act.
Who are you supposed to be now?

135
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:07,330
I'm supposed to be me.

136
00:19:07,490 --> 00:19:10,910
Not like you have a clue
who I am anyway.

137
00:19:18,710 --> 00:19:21,220
I have to work tonight.

138
00:19:21,380 --> 00:19:25,220
I called to tell you, but I was on hold for
ten minutes, and I couldn't wait any longer.

139
00:19:25,390 --> 00:19:28,510
I got him, Eve.

140
00:19:31,270 --> 00:19:33,810
It's over.

141
00:19:33,940 --> 00:19:35,900
It's over.

142
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:40,360
Oh, Sean.

143
00:19:43,650 --> 00:19:47,070
I'll make it up to you
and Jamie. I promise.

144
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:51,410
I'll put in for a desk job... Well, I'll... I'll
do counselling, sit down, talk about Mike...

145
00:19:51,580 --> 00:19:53,710
I'll do it, anything you want.

146
00:19:55,120 --> 00:19:57,500
I just want you.

147
00:19:57,630 --> 00:20:00,380
Well, good, 'cause that's
what you're gonna get.

148
00:20:00,550 --> 00:20:02,380
You happy?

149
00:20:02,550 --> 00:20:04,720
Yes. Yeah.

150
00:20:33,830 --> 00:20:36,040
What is all this?

151
00:20:37,420 --> 00:20:41,090
Sir, the CIA sent this over.

152
00:20:41,250 --> 00:20:44,340
I didn't know they catered.
Send it back.

153
00:20:44,470 --> 00:20:46,720
No, wait.

154
00:20:48,430 --> 00:20:51,100
How about, uh...

155
00:20:51,180 --> 00:20:53,930
What about to Anderson,
Montgomery,

156
00:20:54,100 --> 00:20:56,230
Berkley,

157
00:20:58,350 --> 00:21:02,570
Pincus, Gianelli, Winters...

158
00:21:41,650 --> 00:21:43,610
How's Loomis?

159
00:21:43,730 --> 00:21:47,450
Uh, he's gonna need
a little surgery, but, uh,

160
00:21:47,570 --> 00:21:50,410
he'll be okay.

161
00:21:50,530 --> 00:21:53,530
- What's up?
- Special ops. They want a word.

162
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:55,790
Aw, forget it.
I don't have the time.

163
00:21:55,950 --> 00:21:58,830
Better make time, Sean.

164
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:01,250
Recovered from the jet wreckage.

165
00:22:01,380 --> 00:22:03,460
Found in Pollux Troy's briefcase.

166
00:22:21,770 --> 00:22:23,980
Porcelain casing.

167
00:22:24,110 --> 00:22:25,980
Thermal cloak.

168
00:22:26,110 --> 00:22:29,110
Nerve gas
and biological payload.

169
00:22:29,240 --> 00:22:31,410
It's enough to flatten
a square mile.

170
00:22:31,570 --> 00:22:34,120
Then depending on
the prevailing winds,

171
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:39,210
the fallout'll be a tad worse
than Gulf War syndrome.

172
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:43,830
A biblical...
A biblical plague to LA.

173
00:22:45,460 --> 00:22:48,170
Where is he?
Where is Pollux Troy?

174
00:22:52,380 --> 00:22:55,760
Why draw the schematic if you're
not gonna build the bomb?

175
00:22:55,930 --> 00:22:58,770
What, is it now a crime
in this country to exercise the mind?

176
00:22:58,930 --> 00:23:03,020
- I'm interested in bomb...
- I won't say another word until I see my brother.

177
00:23:04,810 --> 00:23:07,270
Any progress?

178
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:10,160
- I need about ten minutes alone with this guy.
- Ah, give it a rest.

179
00:23:10,240 --> 00:23:12,490
You got Castor. Just go home.

180
00:23:12,660 --> 00:23:14,910
Look, we're not gonna evacuate
the city on your hunch.

181
00:23:15,120 --> 00:23:18,080
Look, I know Castor too well
for this to be a hunch.

182
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:23,210
You know what, just-just run
the goddam bureau any way you like.

183
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:36,010
I could put an agent in his cell.
Maybe Pollux will let it slip.

184
00:23:36,180 --> 00:23:39,850
Oh, come on.
He's a paranoid sociopath.

185
00:23:39,970 --> 00:23:43,440
The only person he'd talk to about
that bomb is his brother, and he's dead.

186
00:23:44,940 --> 00:23:47,520
There is one other possibility.

187
00:24:13,010 --> 00:24:16,470
Oh, God.
You're keeping him alive.

188
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:19,760
Relax, Archer. He's a turnip.

189
00:24:22,480 --> 00:24:24,440
Oh.

190
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:27,900
What if you could walk
into Erewhon Prison...

191
00:24:28,060 --> 00:24:32,280
and give Pollux a nice, big
brotherly hug as Castor Troy?

192
00:24:33,940 --> 00:24:36,240
I have no idea
what you're talking about.

193
00:24:36,410 --> 00:24:39,700
Let me try. Malcolm Walsh.

194
00:24:39,830 --> 00:24:42,410
- I run the bio-cover unit for special ops.
- I know who you are.

195
00:24:42,540 --> 00:24:44,960
- But you don't know what I can do.
- Uh...

196
00:24:45,120 --> 00:24:48,040
Physical alteration.
Augmentation.

197
00:24:48,170 --> 00:24:52,300
Dr Walsh can alter the likeness,
even the voice of a government witness.

198
00:24:52,460 --> 00:24:55,420
I think you'll recognize
this patient.

199
00:24:58,890 --> 00:25:02,390
We had to build your friend Loomis
a whole new ear from scratch.

200
00:25:11,480 --> 00:25:15,280
What we're suggesting for you, Archer,
isn't a permanent transplant like that,

201
00:25:15,400 --> 00:25:18,320
just a temporary trade.

202
00:25:18,490 --> 00:25:20,320
Come here.

203
00:25:22,990 --> 00:25:27,000
With the new anti-inflammatories,
healing takes days, not weeks.

204
00:25:27,160 --> 00:25:29,400
Your blood types won't match,
but Pollux won't know that.

205
00:25:29,500 --> 00:25:32,340
Height difference is negligible.

206
00:25:34,090 --> 00:25:38,930
Skin pigment, eye pigment:
Both almost identical.

207
00:25:39,050 --> 00:25:44,390
We'll use laser shears for the hairline,
microplugs for body hair.

208
00:25:44,560 --> 00:25:49,350
We'll do an abdominoplasti...
take care of those, uh, love handles.

209
00:25:49,480 --> 00:25:53,360
But all that's the easy part.
Here's the real science.

210
00:25:53,570 --> 00:25:56,940
This is a state-of-the-art,
morphogenetic template.

211
00:25:57,030 --> 00:26:00,160
The inside is modeled
on your skull,

212
00:26:00,360 --> 00:26:02,740
the outside exactly like Troy's.

213
00:26:02,870 --> 00:26:06,750
Then we fit his face on top.
Not a replica, but the real thing.

214
00:26:06,870 --> 00:26:09,670
Then we simply connect the muscles,
tear ducts and nerve endings.

215
00:26:09,750 --> 00:26:12,750
- So, you wanna take his face and mine...
- Borrow.

216
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:15,380
The procedure's
completely reversible.

217
00:26:15,550 --> 00:26:18,300
Y-You think that I want
to do this?

218
00:26:18,470 --> 00:26:20,590
- No. No.
- There's no one else, Sean.

219
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:24,140
- No!
- You have lived and breathed Castor Troy for years.

220
00:26:24,260 --> 00:26:26,310
I'll get his gang to talk.
That's what I do.

221
00:26:26,470 --> 00:26:31,440
What if you can't? The bomb will blow,
and Castor Troy will win.

222
00:26:34,690 --> 00:26:37,990
Get out. Go ahead.
Wipe your ass.

223
00:26:38,110 --> 00:26:40,070
Damn, what the hell is
that smell?

224
00:26:40,240 --> 00:26:43,950
He shit in his pants.
Where's Dietrich?

225
00:26:44,070 --> 00:26:48,950
Hello, Sasha. When was the last
time you saw Castor Troy?

226
00:26:49,080 --> 00:26:51,330
- Who cares? He's dead.
- Answer the question.

227
00:26:51,460 --> 00:26:54,000
I know my rights. I don't have
to answer shit.

228
00:26:54,170 --> 00:26:56,090
You're right, but know this:

229
00:26:56,250 --> 00:26:59,670
You're a convicted felon on probation
for harbouring Castor Troy.

230
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:03,340
One phone call from me, and your son
will end up in a foster home.

231
00:27:07,930 --> 00:27:11,730
I understand why
you would use such a threat.

232
00:27:11,890 --> 00:27:14,560
But you try to take him away
from me, I swear to you...

233
00:27:19,860 --> 00:27:23,110
I haven't seen him for years.

234
00:27:37,420 --> 00:27:40,630
This reeks of you. It's got
your signature all over it.

235
00:27:43,130 --> 00:27:47,560
Maybe, but you ain't got nothin'
on me and you know it.

236
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:51,730
Maybe so, but I can keep you
within city limits,

237
00:27:51,890 --> 00:27:53,890
or I can talk
to your sister again.

238
00:27:54,020 --> 00:27:56,810
She's right outside.

239
00:27:56,980 --> 00:27:59,570
Only this time I'll be nice.

240
00:28:00,990 --> 00:28:03,280
