01:27:12,740 --> 01:27:14,910
Eve.

733
01:27:19,990 --> 01:27:22,370
Jesus, Cas!
It's me!

734
01:27:24,120 --> 01:27:26,080
It's me.

735
01:27:27,580 --> 01:27:31,050
Cas. Shh.

736
01:27:31,130 --> 01:27:36,510
Come on.
It's me. Jesus.

737
01:27:39,680 --> 01:27:41,300
Come on.

738
01:27:41,400 --> 01:27:44,810
- Don't you wanna talk?
- The only talk I ever heard from you is...

739
01:27:44,940 --> 01:27:48,020
"Suck my tongue," "I love
your ass," and "See ya,"

740
01:27:48,150 --> 01:27:51,270
and take the filthy shit off,
put this on and get outta here.

741
01:27:51,400 --> 01:27:54,440
- No, I'm not goin' anywhere.
- Oh, really?

742
01:27:54,530 --> 01:27:56,360
What do you... What do you
expect me, after all this time...

743
01:27:56,490 --> 01:27:59,450
Just to... Just to
jump on you?

744
01:27:59,570 --> 01:28:01,620
- That's not what I...
- Is that what you expect?

745
01:28:01,700 --> 01:28:03,540
- That's not what I meant.
- What did you mean?

746
01:28:03,660 --> 01:28:07,120
- I meant...
- Huh? Is this what you meant?

747
01:28:07,210 --> 01:28:10,750
That? That? How about this?
Is that good? Huh?

748
01:28:17,470 --> 01:28:19,300
- Sean Archer.
- Bro.

749
01:28:19,430 --> 01:28:22,470
Well, I figured he might drop in
on some of our old friends.

750
01:28:22,560 --> 01:28:26,850
And if my eyes don't deceive, I think this
fellow's beginning to enjoy being you.

751
01:28:28,020 --> 01:28:29,900
Good.

752
01:28:36,740 --> 01:28:40,240
Look, look, look. Okay.
L-Look, Sasha.

753
01:28:41,990 --> 01:28:45,410
What I meant is, uh, that
I'm not going anywhere...

754
01:28:45,540 --> 01:28:48,290
until your brother
helps me, uh, first.

755
01:28:50,960 --> 01:28:54,250
Cas. If the FBI finds out
that you were here,

756
01:28:54,380 --> 01:28:57,050
I'll lose my son.

757
01:28:57,170 --> 01:28:59,050
Please, Cas, you just gotta go.

758
01:29:05,640 --> 01:29:08,640
I've said and done some things
that have made your life harder.

759
01:29:08,730 --> 01:29:11,350
- I know.
- How would you?

760
01:29:11,440 --> 01:29:13,860
When you left,
you never looked back.

761
01:29:13,940 --> 01:29:15,860
I... I just know.

762
01:29:27,700 --> 01:29:31,880
Look, Sasha, I'm not
the same person you remember.

763
01:29:32,000 --> 01:29:34,420
And for what it's worth,
I'm sorry.

764
01:29:40,800 --> 01:29:43,390
- They're nice-looking clothes.
- Yeah, of course. They're yours.

765
01:29:43,550 --> 01:29:46,310
Look, I know, I...

766
01:29:46,430 --> 01:29:48,560
just like 'em.

767
01:29:49,810 --> 01:29:53,560
That's a nice-lookin' kid too.

768
01:29:53,650 --> 01:29:56,070
Yeah. Of course.

769
01:29:57,900 --> 01:30:00,240
He's yours too.

770
01:30:19,300 --> 01:30:21,800
- How old is he?
- Five.

771
01:30:23,590 --> 01:30:26,050
Nobody knows he's yours.
I was...

772
01:30:26,180 --> 01:30:29,640
scared someone would try
to hurt him just to hurt you.

773
01:30:29,770 --> 01:30:32,440
Adam. Adam.

774
01:30:32,560 --> 01:30:35,900
Don't want you playing with those
things. They are very, very dangerous.

775
01:30:36,020 --> 01:30:40,280
Okay? Now come on, sweetie.

776
01:30:40,400 --> 01:30:44,320
I want you to meet your father.

777
01:30:44,450 --> 01:30:47,780
Look at him.
It's okay. Say hi.

778
01:30:47,910 --> 01:30:49,790
Hi.

779
01:31:06,090 --> 01:31:08,640
Hi.

780
01:31:12,180 --> 01:31:15,100
Michael.

781
01:31:15,190 --> 01:31:18,230
- Michael. Michael?
- Cas.

782
01:31:18,320 --> 01:31:21,440
- Cas. Cas, you're scaring him.
- Michael?

783
01:31:21,570 --> 01:31:24,450
Let him go.

784
01:31:24,570 --> 01:31:27,320
What is the matter with you?

785
01:31:30,580 --> 01:31:32,830
Get down!

786
01:31:44,130 --> 01:31:46,720
Okay, Red Team!
Red Team, break off!

787
01:31:46,840 --> 01:31:50,260
How'd you get to be so brave?
How'd you get to be so brave?

788
01:31:52,930 --> 01:31:54,980
- Come out now with your hands up!
- Put these on.

789
01:31:55,060 --> 01:31:58,270
Okay. That's a good idea,
baby. Listen to your music.

790
01:31:58,360 --> 01:31:59,980
- Come on.
- Come out now!

791
01:32:00,110 --> 01:32:02,530
<i>♪ Somewhere ♪</i>

792
01:32:02,650 --> 01:32:04,610
- Go! Go! Go!
- We have a warrant for your arrest!

793
01:32:06,240 --> 01:32:08,700
Cops.

794
01:32:10,950 --> 01:32:13,790
I hate cops.

795
01:32:13,870 --> 01:32:16,370
Come on, kid.

796
01:32:23,880 --> 01:32:28,180
- Move! Move!
- Go left, left! First door to the right!

797
01:32:33,560 --> 01:32:35,060
Go! Go! Go!

798
01:32:36,390 --> 01:32:37,890
Go! Go!

799
01:32:50,340 --> 01:32:53,660
♪ Someday I'll wish
upon a star

800
01:32:53,740 --> 01:32:56,790
Let's get outta here! Come on.

801
01:32:57,870 --> 01:32:59,580
Don't shoot! Don't shoot!

802
01:33:13,310 --> 01:33:14,930
Damn, my place
is gettin' fucked up.

803
01:33:25,230 --> 01:33:26,860
Take him.

804
01:33:36,580 --> 01:33:39,250
Cas! Cas,
give me the boy!

805
01:33:42,830 --> 01:33:46,460
Really? Really?
Come on! Shit!

806
01:33:48,300 --> 01:33:50,840
Come on, come on!
Let's go! Go, go, go!

807
01:33:57,310 --> 01:33:59,230
Cas, be careful with him!

808
01:34:09,110 --> 01:34:12,560
Don't be scared, All right? All right?

809
01:34:12,950 --> 01:34:18,870
♪ Somewhere over the rainbow

810
01:34:18,950 --> 01:34:24,920
♪ Skies are blue

811
01:34:27,960 --> 01:34:30,760
♪ And the dreams

812
01:34:30,840 --> 01:34:34,970
♪ That you dared to dream

813
01:34:35,100 --> 01:34:41,310
♪ Really do come true

814
01:34:41,440 --> 01:34:45,270
♪ Someday I'll wish
upon a star

815
01:34:45,400 --> 01:34:48,320
♪ And wake up
where the clouds

816
01:34:48,440 --> 01:34:52,110
Adam!

817
01:34:52,200 --> 01:34:55,740
♪ Me

818
01:34:56,780 --> 01:35:03,920
♪ Birds fly over the rainbow

819
01:35:04,000 --> 01:35:07,130
♪ Why then, oh, why

820
01:35:07,210 --> 01:35:11,470
♪ Can't I

821
01:35:11,510 --> 01:35:14,180
Adam! Adam!

822
01:35:15,430 --> 01:35:18,220
Get him out back!
Go, go, go!

823
01:35:21,980 --> 01:35:23,640
Put the boy down.

824
01:35:23,730 --> 01:35:26,440
Honey, sweetie,
don't touch that.

825
01:35:26,610 --> 01:35:28,110
It isn't nice!

826
01:35:28,270 --> 01:35:30,320
I don't ever
wanna see you do that.

827
01:35:33,570 --> 01:35:36,160
They're like cockroaches!

828
01:35:36,240 --> 01:35:38,120
Hey. Drop it.

829
01:35:39,660 --> 01:35:41,580
That's it.

830
01:35:43,870 --> 01:35:45,580
Buzz.

831
01:35:45,670 --> 01:35:47,170
Hey!

832
01:35:52,300 --> 01:35:54,340
Told him not to fuck with me.

833
01:36:40,720 --> 01:36:42,680
Take the boy and get outta here.

834
01:36:42,760 --> 01:36:44,680
- Are you all right?
- Go!

835
01:36:49,690 --> 01:36:51,820
Hurry up.

836
01:36:57,240 --> 01:37:00,200
Hey, man.

837
01:37:00,320 --> 01:37:02,950
We had some good times,
didn't we?

838
01:37:37,820 --> 01:37:42,240
I don't know what I hate
wearing worse:

839
01:37:42,370 --> 01:37:44,580
Your face or your body.

840
01:37:46,830 --> 01:37:49,250
I mean, I enjoy
boning your wife,

841
01:37:49,330 --> 01:37:51,290
but, uh, well, let's face it.

842
01:37:51,420 --> 01:37:55,670
We both like it better
the other way, yes?

843
01:37:55,800 --> 01:37:57,760
So why don't we just trade back.

844
01:37:57,920 --> 01:38:00,220
You can't give back
what you've taken from me.

845
01:38:02,140 --> 01:38:06,430
Oh, well.
Plan "B."

846
01:38:06,560 --> 01:38:08,560
Let's just kill each other.

847
01:40:11,810 --> 01:40:15,390
Sir, why are you so upset?

848
01:40:15,520 --> 01:40:17,980
It's just Pollux Troy.

849
01:40:46,630 --> 01:40:50,510
Sir, look. You're
on the cover of Time.

850
01:40:50,600 --> 01:40:52,760
Listen. "In a single week,
Agent Sean Archer...

851
01:40:52,810 --> 01:40:55,130
"has ordered a stunning series
of blitzkrieg-style raids...

852
01:40:55,140 --> 01:40:58,770
"on the hideouts, staging grounds and
safe houses of our nation's assassins.

853
01:40:58,940 --> 01:41:00,900
Car bombs..."

854
01:41:04,650 --> 01:41:08,450
Sean. Look we're friends,
so I'm gonna tell you face to face.

855
01:41:08,490 --> 01:41:11,240
I don't give a damn if you are
Time's Man of the Year.

856
01:41:11,370 --> 01:41:15,660
After last night's bloodbath,
I'm terminatin' your war on terrorists.

857
01:41:20,460 --> 01:41:25,420
Is that, uh, because I'm getting
all the kudos and you're not?

858
01:41:25,510 --> 01:41:28,110
Jesus Christ. I don't know where
you're gettin' your intelligence.

859
01:41:28,220 --> 01:41:32,350
It's not from field agents.
Sometimes I think you know too much.

860
01:41:32,470 --> 01:41:34,510
Washington's starting to worry.

861
01:41:34,640 --> 01:41:38,940
Justice wants a hearing.
Shoot.

862
01:41:39,020 --> 01:41:42,020
They're concerned about the
constitutionality of your gestapo tactics!

863
01:41:42,150 --> 01:41:44,520
And frankly,
so am I! I'm...

864
01:41:46,940 --> 01:41:48,990
Uh, okay, Victor,

865
01:41:49,110 --> 01:41:52,950
I'll give the, uh,
taxpayers a break.

866
01:41:53,070 --> 01:41:55,040
But, um,

867
01:41:57,330 --> 01:42:00,620
I have something, uh,
I want to confess.

868
01:42:00,750 --> 01:42:03,920
And I don't think
you're gonna like it.

869
01:42:04,000 --> 01:42:06,420
I am Castor Troy.

870
01:42:17,600 --> 01:42:20,600
- Kimmy. Kim?
- Yes, sir.

871
01:42:20,690 --> 01:42:24,020
Call the paramedics. Victor
Lazarro's had a heart attack.

872
01:42:24,150 --> 01:42:26,320
- Oh, God. Right away.
- Thank you.

873
01:42:52,180 --> 01:42:54,090
Home.

874
01:43:17,660 --> 01:43:19,540
Eve.

875
01:43:21,960 --> 01:43:23,830
Eve.

876
01:43:23,920 --> 01:43:26,540
No. Honey, please,
please don't scream.

877
01:43:26,670 --> 01:43:28,550
Don't scream.
I'm not gonna hurt you.

878
01:43:28,670 --> 01:43:31,260
Okay, just don't,
don't, don't, don't.

879
01:43:31,380 --> 01:43:33,470
Just don't...
don't look at my face.

880
01:43:33,630 --> 01:43:36,800
And the voice.
Don't listen.

881
01:43:36,890 --> 01:43:40,060
- Just...
- I know who you are! You killed our son!

882
01:43:40,220 --> 01:43:42,810
I did not kill our son.

883
01:43:42,980 --> 01:43:44,850
I'm Sean.

884
01:43:49,940 --> 01:43:52,780
The last time I saw you...

885
01:43:52,860 --> 01:43:54,910
was in this room.

886
01:43:54,990 --> 01:43:58,620
We had a fight when I said
I had to go away again.

887
01:43:58,700 --> 01:44:01,790
And I spent the night
in Mike's old bed.

888
01:44:14,970 --> 01:44:17,550
I'm tired, Eve.

889
01:44:17,680 --> 01:44:22,270
The assignment was to enter
a federal prison as Castor Troy.

890
01:44:22,390 --> 01:44:25,350
It's just fucking insane.

891
01:44:25,440 --> 01:44:29,520
And it's... A special ops
surgeon, uh, gave me, uh,

892
01:44:29,650 --> 01:44:31,650
Castor's face!

893
01:44:34,400 --> 01:44:38,070
Then, uh... And then, somehow,
Castor came out of his, uh,

894
01:44:39,870 --> 01:44:44,540
his-his coma, and
he killed everybody...

895
01:44:44,620 --> 01:44:46,870
who knew about the mission.

896
01:44:47,000 --> 01:44:50,750
But, but not before
transforming into me.

897
01:45:12,770 --> 01:45:16,610
I know you don't believe a word
I'm saying. Well, here's proof, Doctor.

898
01:45:16,740 --> 01:45:20,570
Your husband, me, my,
Sean's blood type is O-negative.

899
01:45:20,700 --> 01:45:23,410
Castor's is AB.

900
01:45:32,710 --> 01:45:35,340
And I love you.

901
01:45:49,310 --> 01:45:51,230
Get some backup.

902
01:45:55,860 --> 01:45:58,400
What a day.

903
01:46:01,780 --> 01:46:04,580
You look tense.

904
01:46:08,960 --> 01:46:13,290
I know I've been acting
different lately. Strange.

905
01:46:14,800 --> 01:46:18,510
I've got a confession
to make, Eve.

906
01:46:18,630 --> 01:46:21,640
You're not gonna like it.

907
01:46:21,680 --> 01:46:25,140
Oh, Eve. I feel...
I feel so close to you.

908
01:46:26,680 --> 01:46:30,060
I read your diary. I know
I shouldn't have. I'm ashamed.

909
01:46:30,190 --> 01:46:32,230
But I did.

910
01:46:32,350 --> 01:46:34,940
I just wanna be the man
that you deserve...

911
01:46:35,110 --> 01:46:37,650
passionate, tender.

912
01:46:41,780 --> 01:46:45,530
Victor Lazarro died today.
He had a heart seizure.

913
01:46:45,660 --> 01:46:48,540
My mentor, gone.

914
01:46:49,870 --> 01:46:52,330
First Tito, then Victor.
So what?

915
01:46:55,090 --> 01:46:57,880
I hope this doesn't mean
I'm losing you.

916
01:46:58,000 --> 01:46:59,880
Of course not.

917
01:47:07,810 --> 01:47:10,430
You're the only family I've got.

918
01:48:00,780 --> 01:48:02,690
Oh, God.

919
01:48:06,740 --> 01:48:11,330
- Oh, God.
- I was hoping you'd come here.

920
01:48:11,410 --> 01:48:14,160
Thank you for trusting me.

921
01:48:16,750 --> 01:48:22,010
Right now, I don't trust anyone.

922
01:48:22,090 --> 01:48:25,180
Eve, wh-where'd
you get that gun?

923
01:48:25,260 --> 01:48:27,470
I took it from my fake husband.

924
01:48:27,590 --> 01:48:30,850
Put it down.
You know I'm Sean.

925
01:48:30,930 --> 01:48:34,600
Do I? Maybe Sean's
already dead, huh?

926
01:48:34,730 --> 01:48:37,650
I'm moving very slowly.

927
01:49:00,670 --> 01:49:04,170
I was thinking
the other day, I...

928
01:49:04,260 --> 01:49:06,170
I remember...

929
01:49:06,300 --> 01:49:09,390
I once took a date out...

930
01:49:09,550 --> 01:49:11,600
for surf and turf,

931
01:49:11,760 --> 01:49:15,730
not knowing she was
a vegetarian.

932
01:49:15,770 --> 01:49:20,360
So she ate bread.

933
01:49:20,440 --> 01:49:23,650
And, uh, and broke her tooth
on a rye seed.

934
01:49:27,240 --> 01:49:30,620
And we, we drove around
all night,

935
01:49:30,700 --> 01:49:34,700
uh, looking for a...
for a all-night dentist.

936
01:49:34,790 --> 01:49:38,330
And, and he, uh...
He was so drunk,

937
01:49:38,460 --> 01:49:41,000
he fixed the wrong tooth.

938
01:49:46,970 --> 01:49:50,590
And it... When I
finally brought her home...

939
01:49:53,810 --> 01:49:59,190
Even though it must have
hurt like hell,

940
01:49:59,310 --> 01:50:02,900
you, you, you kissed me.

941
01:50:14,700 --> 01:50:18,370
Sean,

942
01:50:18,500 --> 01:50:22,330
that man...

943
01:50:22,460 --> 01:50:25,750
You know we've been living
together as man and wife for a week.

944
01:50:25,840 --> 01:50:28,670
Yeah, I...

945
01:50:28,800 --> 01:50:33,430
I know.
Eve. Eve.

946
01:50:33,510 --> 01:50:36,470
I put you
in that position and, and...

947
01:50:36,560 --> 01:50:39,310
I-I-I can never
make it up to you.

948
01:50:46,190 --> 01:50:48,860
Well, you're damn well
gonna try.

949
01:50:48,990 --> 01:50:51,820
Let me take a look at that wound
before you bleed to death.

950
01:50:59,410 --> 01:51:01,670
With Lazarro out of the way,

951
01:51:01,790 --> 01:51:04,840
Castor's the new acting director
of the Bureau.

952
01:51:04,920 --> 01:51:08,170
- He's untouchable.
- Not tomorrow.

953
01:51:08,300 --> 01:51:10,470
Tomorrow he'll
be at Victor's service.

954
01:51:10,550 --> 01:51:14,180
Tomorrow.

955
01:51:14,300 --> 01:51:16,680
That will be the day.

956
01:51:20,390 --> 01:51:22,940
I want you and Jamie away from
there. Give him a good excuse.

957
01:51:23,060 --> 01:51:24,940
I can cover for Jamie,

958
01:51:25,060 --> 01:51:27,341
but if I'm not coming he's
gonna know that something's up.

959
01:51:29,110 --> 01:51:31,860
And besides, I'm the only one
who can try and explain the truth.

960
01:51:33,780 --> 01:51:36,830
Excuse me, Mr Archer.
May I help you?

961
01:51:36,910 --> 01:51:39,080
Dr Levine to X Ray.

962
01:51:51,010 --> 01:51:53,630
Sean, what are you doing here?

963
01:51:59,060 --> 01:52:01,770
Sorry, darling, it...

964
01:52:01,930 --> 01:52:05,400
I just get so, so jealous, I...

965
01:52:05,440 --> 01:52:08,150
I mean, wh-wh-what is a guy
to think when his, uh,

966
01:52:08,270 --> 01:52:10,150
his wife runs off
in the middle of the night?

967
01:52:10,280 --> 01:52:13,490
That I'm a doctor that's on call,
so please let me get back to work, okay?

968
01:52:13,570 --> 01:52:15,490
Sorry.

969
01:52:18,910 --> 01:52:23,080
Lies, distrust, mixed messages.

970
01:52:23,210 --> 01:52:25,120
This is turning
into a real marriage.

971
01:52:45,770 --> 01:52:49,650
How's Adam?

972
01:52:49,770 --> 01:52:53,110
I took him over to my cousin's
until this whole thing blows over.

973
01:52:53,240 --> 01:52:55,740
- Where's Jamie?
- That's what I'd like to know.

974
01:52:55,820 --> 01:52:58,620
She stole $50 from my purse
and took off.

975
01:53:00,910 --> 01:53:05,080
- So what's the next move?
- This isn't your fight.

976
01:53:05,210 --> 01:53:08,750
Oh, come on. You're surprised? Our
daughter won't even visit Michael's grave.

977
01:53:08,830 --> 01:53:11,290
You think she gives a damn
about your boss?

978
01:53:16,970 --> 01:53:21,100
He killed my brother. I'm not
gonna let him take you too.

979
01:53:35,820 --> 01:53:40,620
Whatever happens, I promise...

980
01:53:40,700 --> 01:53:43,410
Sean Archer is
